dct_description_sm: New Jersey. Department of Conservation and Development. Division ofGeology and Topography. Atlas Sheet 34 (1936) New Jersey Geological Survey. Relief show by 10 ft. contour interval and spot heights. Depth shown by 10 ft. contour interval at mean low tide. Original survey 1886, principal culture revised 1910, 1927, 1935. Original survey and revisions made under direction of C. C. Vermeule, Topographer. Revision of 1935 by L. P. Plummer, Topographic Engineer. Title is not given. Region covered: southern Salem County and western Cumberland County.
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : New Jersey Geological Survey, 1936.
